definition.value: A quinolinemonocarboxylic acid having the carboxy group at position 7 as well as oxo and ethyl groups at positions 4 and 1 respectively and a dioxolo ring fused at the 5- and 6-positions. A synthetic antibiotic, it is used in veterinary medicine for the treatment of bacterial infections in cattle, pigs and poultry.
A trichothecene mycotoxin that is T-2 toxin in which the acetyloxy group at position 4S has been hydrolysed to the corresponding hydroxy group. It is the major metabolite of T-2 toxin.
Any compound that induces the process of autophagy (the self-digestion of one or more components of a cell through the action of enzymes originating within the same cell).
a D-fructofuranose 1-phosphate(2-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of beta-D-fructofuranose 1-phosphate; major species at pH 7.3.

A hydroxamic acid that is (3S)-N-hydroxy-2,2-dimethylthiomorpholine-3-carboxamide in which the hydrogen attached to the thiomorpholine nitrogen has been replaced by a [4-(pyridin-4-yloxy)phenyl]sulfonyl group. It is a selective inhibitor with of matrix metalloproteinases (MMPs) 2, 3, 9, 13, and 14.
An organic cation resulting from the protonation of prinomastat.
An antagonist that binds to and blocks the activity of prostaglandin receptors.
A 4-oxo monocarboxylic acid that is 4-oxobutanoic acid in which the pro-R hydrogen at position 3 has been replaced by a hydroxy group.

A non-proteinogenic L-alpha-amino acid that is L-norleucine which is substituted at position 5 by an oxo group and at position 6 by a diazo group. It is as inhibitor of various glutamine-utilising enzymes.
A diterpenyl phosphate that is the 15-O-diphospho derivative of peregrinol.
An inositol phosphophytoceramide(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any inositol C20 phosphophytoceramide; major species at pH 7.3.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) having an acyl group attached to the ceramide nitrogen and hydroxylation at C4 of the C20 sphingoid base; major species at pH 7.3.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer(d18:0); major species at pH 7.3.
A mannosylinositol phosphorylceramide(1-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of any Man-1-6-Ins-1-P-Cer(d20:0); major species at pH 7.3.
